---
const faqs = [
  {
    category: "Going Solo",
    items: [
      { q: "Will I be the only solo traveler on the ship?", a: "Not even close. Every sailing we host is filled with solo travelers — that's the whole point. You'll be surrounded by people in the same boat (literally). Most of our travelers come alone and leave with group chats, follow-up trips already planned, and friendships that outlast the voyage." },
      { q: "What if I'm shy or introverted?", a: "We've heard this one a lot. Many of our most popular repeat travelers describe themselves as introverted. The difference here: you're not cold-calling strangers. We introduce you before you board via our private group chat, so by the time you step on the ship, you already know faces and names. The first conversation is never the hardest." },
      { q: "What age range goes on these sailings?", a: "We welcome adults of all ages — our travelers range from their 20s to their 70s. The vibe shifts by sailing (check the Vibe Tag on each cruise card), so if you're looking for a high-energy social sailing or a more laid-back adventure, we'll match you to the right one." },
      { q: "Do I have to participate in every group activity?", a: "Absolutely not. We build the social infrastructure — mixers, group dinners, hosted excursions — but your itinerary is yours. Want to spend a shore day wandering solo? Skip the group dinner for a quiet meal? That's completely fine. Community on your terms." },
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Pricing & The Single Supplement",
    items: [
      { q: "What is the single supplement?", a: "Cruise lines price their cabins assuming two people sharing. When you travel solo, many lines charge you a 'single supplement' — sometimes 100% extra — to make up the difference. It means you end up paying double for a cabin you're using alone. We negotiate group rates and solo-specific inventory that dramatically reduce or eliminate this penalty." },
      { q: "How much does a hosted sailing cost?", a: "It depends on the cruise line, destination, cabin category, and how far in advance you book. Prices on our cruise cards show starting rates for interior cabins. We always recommend booking early — solo-specific inventory is limited and sells out faster than standard cabins. Contact us for a current quote on any sailing." },
      { q: "What's included in the price?", a: "The cruise fare covers your cabin, onboard meals at main dining venues, most entertainment, and port calls. Not included: flights, pre/post-cruise hotels, specialty dining, shore excursions, gratuities, and travel insurance (which we strongly recommend). We can help bundle any of these — just ask." },
      { q: "Should I get travel insurance?", a: "Yes. We'd never tell you it's optional. Medical evacuations at sea are expensive. Cancellations happen. We recommend purchasing travel insurance within 14 days of your initial deposit to maximize coverage, including pre-existing condition waivers. We can connect you with trusted providers." },
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Booking & Logistics",
    items: [
      { q: "How do I book a sailing?", a: "Start with a conversation — use the chat widget or the Plan Your Voyage button to reach us. We'll walk you through available sailings, cabin options, and pricing, then handle the booking from there. No forms. No booking engines. A real person, start to finish." },
      { q: "Can you help with flights and pre-cruise hotels?", a: "Yes. We can coordinate airfare, hotel stays before or after your cruise, and airport transfers. Some travelers like to arrive a day early to explore the departure city — we can build that in. Just let us know what you need." },
      { q: "What cruise lines do you work with?", a: "We work across the major lines — Norwegian Cruise Line, Royal Caribbean, Celebrity, Carnival, MSC, and more — wherever we can secure solo-friendly group rates and hosted group space. The cruise line varies by sailing; what stays consistent is our team onboard every departure." },
      { q: "How far in advance should I book?", a: "As early as possible. Solo cabin inventory is genuinely limited — when a ship has 20 solo-friendly cabins and we're filling a group, they go fast. Most of our travelers book 6–12 months out. That said, we occasionally have last-minute spots open up — ask us what's available." },
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Onboard Experience",
    items: [
      { q: "What does 'fully hosted' actually mean?", a: "It means one of our team members sails with you. They're not a tour guide — they're the connector. They run the welcome mixer, coordinate group dinners, organize optional shared excursions, and make sure nobody feels like they're on their own. Think of it as having a friend on the ship who knows everybody." },
      { q: "Will I have to share a cabin?", a: "No. Every traveler gets their own cabin. Solo supplement pricing means you pay for your own space — no roommate matching unless you specifically request it to save money (we can accommodate that too)." },
      { q: "What are the 'Vibe Tags' on the cruise cards?", a: "'High-Social Mixer' sailings are event-heavy with lots of group programming. 'The Lore-Builder' sailings lean into destination and culture — more port time, more exploration, a slightly quieter ship vibe. 'Main Character Energy' means you're going to have a story to tell. The Independence Meter on each card shows how structured vs. free-form the experience is." },
    ]
  },
];
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>FAQ — The Solo Cruisers</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Everything you want to know about sailing solo with The Solo Cruisers — single supplements explained, what's included, how booking works, and what 'fully hosted' actually means." />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://thesolocruisers.com/faq" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="FAQ — The Solo Cruisers" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="Single supplements, solo cabin inventory, what's included, how booking works — all your questions answered." />
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1530103862676-de8c9debad1d?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&h=630&q=80" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;1,9..144,400&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&family=Poppins:wght@800&family=Pacifico&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    :root {
      --navy: #173a5e; --ink: #173a5e; --ink-soft: #2a3a52;
      --cream: #faf6ef; --cream-deep: #f1e9dc;
      --brass: #b8893f; --brass-light: #c8a14e;
      --teal: #46bcd0; --text: #2a2a28; --muted: #6f6f68; --line: #e3dccf;
    }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }
    body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); background: var(--cream); line-height: 1.6; }
    h1, h2, h3 { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.1; }
    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
    .wrap { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
    .wrap-nav { max-width: 1240px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
    .eyebrow { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--brass); margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block; }

    /* NAV */
    .nav { padding: 1.2rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--cream); position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 50; }
    .nav-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
    .brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .brand-svg { width: 42px; height: 42px; }
    .brand-name { font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--navy); text-transform: uppercase; }
    .nav-links { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.8rem; }
    .nav-links a { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink-soft); transition: color 0.2s; }
    .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--brass); }
    .btn-pill { background: var(--teal); color: #fff !important; padding: 0.55rem 1.3rem; border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600 !important; transition: background 0.25s; }
    .btn-pill:hover { background: var(--navy) !important; }

    /* PAGE HERO */
    .page-hero { background: var(--ink); color: var(--cream); padding: 5rem 0 4rem; text-align: center; }
    .page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem,5vw,3.6rem); color: var(--cream); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .page-hero p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; }

    /* FAQ */
    .faq-section { padding: 5rem 0 6rem; }
    .faq-category { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }
    .faq-category-title { font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--brass); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; padding-bottom: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--brass); display: inline-block; }
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
    .faq-btn {
      width: 100%; text-align: left; background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer;
      padding: 1.35rem 0; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
      font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.08rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink);
      gap: 1rem; transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .faq-btn:hover { color: var(--brass); }
    .faq-btn[aria-expanded="true"] { color: var(--brass); }
    .faq-icon { flex-shrink: 0; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--brass); line-height: 1; transition: transform 0.3s ease; font-style: normal; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 300; }
    .faq-btn[aria-expanded="true"] .faq-icon { transform: rotate(45deg); }
    .faq-answer { overflow: hidden; max-height: 0; transition: max-height 0.4s ease; }
    .faq-answer-inner { padding: 0 0 1.5rem; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.85; max-width: 720px; }

    /* CTA */
    .cta-band { background: var(--cream-deep); padding: 5rem 0; text-align: center; }
    .cta-band h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.6rem); margin-bottom: 0.9rem; }
    .cta-band p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .btn-solid { background: var(--teal); color: #fff; padding: 0.95rem 2.4rem; border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; display: inline-block; transition: background 0.25s, transform 0.25s; }
    .btn-solid:hover { background: var(--navy); transform: translateY(-2px); }

    /* FOOTER */
    footer { background: var(--ink); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); padding: 3rem 0 2rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.82rem; }
    footer a { color: var(--brass-light); }

    @media (max-width: 940px) { .nav-links { display: none; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="nav">
    <div class="wrap-nav nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="brand">
        <div class="brand-svg">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect width="100" height="100" rx="24" fill="#46BCD0"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="46" fill="white"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="34" stroke="white" stroke-width="22"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="34" stroke="#E5443B" stroke-width="22" stroke-dasharray="26.7 26.7" transform="rotate(45 50 50)"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="45" stroke="#173A5E" stroke-width="3"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="23" stroke="#173A5E" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M41 55 H59 L57 60 Q56 63 53 63 H47 Q44 63 43 60 Z" fill="white" stroke="#173A5E" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <rect x="46" y="49" width="8" height="6" fill="white" stroke="#173A5E" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <rect x="50" y="45" width="4" height="4" fill="#FF7A4D" stroke="#173A5E" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <span class="brand-name">Solo Cruisers</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="/#story">Why Us</a>
        <a href="/#cruises">Cruises</a>
        <a href="/destinations">Destinations</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-pill">Plan Your Voyage</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--brass-light);">Frequently Asked Questions</span>
      <h1>Everything you want to know<br>before you book.</h1>
      <p>Can't find what you're looking for? Use the chat widget or reach out directly — a real person will answer.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="wrap">
      {faqs.map(group => (
        <div class="faq-category">
          <div class="faq-category-title">{group.category}</div>
          {group.items.map((item, i) => (
            <div class="faq-item">
              <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" data-faq>
                {item.q}
                <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
              </button>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <div class="faq-answer-inner">{item.a}</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Still have questions?</span>
      <h2>Talk to a real person.</h2>
      <p>No bots, no ticketing systems. Just a conversation about where you want to go.</p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-solid">Plan Your Voyage →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="wrap">
      <p>© 2026 The Solo Cruisers · <a href="/about">About</a> · <a href="/faq">FAQ</a></p>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq]').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const expanded = btn.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        // Close all
        document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq]').forEach(b => {
          b.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          b.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight = '0';
        });
        // Open clicked if it was closed
        if (!expanded) {
          btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
          btn.nextElementSibling.style.maxHeight = btn.nextElementSibling.scrollHeight + 'px';
        }
      });
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
